Table Name --- PRIMARY KEY
Customers  --- Cust_ID
Products   --- Pro_ID
Employees  --- Emp_ID
Orders     --- Ord_ID
    Orders Table as Columns Cust_ID, Pro_ID, Emp_ID which is the reference from Customers, Products, Employees Tables Primary key 

Foreign Key : Is a Primary key in its respective Parent Tables but To interconnect with its Child tables these Primary key will be Foreign Key.

    Examples: Cust_ID, Pro_ID, Emp_ID are Foreign keys inside Orders.

> ALTER TABLE ADD FOREIGN KEY (Pro_ID) REFERENCES Products  

> ALTER TABLE ADD CONSTRAINT Pro_ID FOREIGN KEY (Pro_ID) REFERENCES Products(Pro_ID)